 > **†** FlashInfer uses TRTLLM attention on Blackwell (SM100), which supports sinks. Disable via `--attention-config.use_trtllm_attention=0`.
 >
+> **‡** `FLASHINFER_FMHA_V2` keeps the fp8 KV-cache only for memory savings: K/V are dequantized to BF16 on the fly (using the per-tensor k/v scales) and the attention kernel runs in BF16. There is no fp8 attention compute, so expect added per-step dequant overhead rather than a matmul speedup.
+>
 > **\*** Specify the FlashAttention version via `--attention-config.flash_attn_version=2`, `3`, or `4`. Default is FA4 on SM100+ (Blackwell), FA3 on SM90 (Hopper), FA2 otherwise.
 
